title: Stade Municipal de Djourbel
text:
Stade Municipal de Djourbel or Stade Ely Manel Fall is a multi-use <a href="stadium">stadium</a> in <a href="Diourbel">Diourbel</a> (sometimes as Djourbel), <a href="Senegal">Senegal</a>. It is currently used mostly for <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a> matches and serves as a home ground of <a href="ASC%20SUNEOR">ASC SUNEOR</a>, also Diamono Djourbel plays at the stadium. The stadium holds 5,000 people.
One of the two continental matches was played at the stadium, the first three were the African Cup of Champions Clubs and the last was the CAF Champions League in <a href="African%20Cup%20of%20Champions%20Clubs%201981">1981</a>, <a href="African%20Cup%20of%20Champions%20Clubs%201984">1984</a>, <a href="African%20Cup%20of%20Champions%20Clubs%201988">1988</a> and <a href="1997%20CAF%20Champions%20League">1997</a>. The last two were cup competitions played in <a href="2002%20African%20Cup%20Winners%27%20Cup">2002</a> and in <a href="2003%20CAF%20Cup">2003</a>, the first was the African Cup Winner's Cup and the second was the CAF Cup.
